main event: A blue-green round object, resembling the exhaust of an F4D but traveling at a much greater speed, was observed in the sky south of Oceanside, California.
interesting points: The object was the size of a half-dollar.,The sighting lasted for approximately 2 seconds.,It appeared brighter than any other aircraft.,Commander Moore estimated the object's speed to be Mach 2 or 3 if it was close.,This was the second sighting reported that night in the San Diego area.
witness description: Commander Moore, flying an A3D at North Island NAS, reported the sighting.
